Ad [Addendum] Sermon of St. John. Gipsy woman with flat wide brimmed hat and naked child see: 'Habites variarom orbis gentium' 1581, engraving by Julius Goltzius after J.J. [Jean Jacques] Boissard in collection of Costume engravings, B.M. [...] , fol. 115 [...] Zigeunerin auss Orient'. The same figure reversed in woodcut in Cesare VECELLIO, Habiti antichi et moderni, Venice 1598 (2nd ed. 1st ed. of 1591 not seen), fol. 471v. text fol. 472r. 'Mulier orientalis quae vulga cingana dicitur.'
